


Basic HTML Page                                    

<!DOCTYPE html>                                    tells browser you are using HTML5

<html>                                             root of an html document

<head>                                             container for metadata

<title>My First Page</title>                       page title

</head>                                            

<body>                                             contains all data rendered by the browser

<p>hello world</p>                                 paragraph tag

</body>

</html>


HTML is NOT case sensitive




Heading Tag

Used to display headings in HTML

h1      (most important)     (this is the largest in font size)

h2

h3

h4

h5

h6       (least important)      (size decreases as we go down and it is smallest)





types of tags :

i) Paragraph Tag

Used to add paragraphs in HTML

<p> This is a sample paragraph </p>



ii) Anchor Tag

Used to add links to your page

<a href="https://google.com"> Google </a>



iii) Image Tag

Used to add images to your page

<img src="/image.png" alt="Random Image">
               ||
         (relative url)



iv) Bold, Italic & Underline Tags

Used to highlight text in your page

<b> Bold </b>

<i> Italic </i>

<u> Underline </u>



v) Big & Small Tags

Used to display big & small text on your page

<big> Big </big>

<small> Small </small>



vi) Hr Tag

Used to display a horizontal ruler, used to separate content

<hr>



vii) Subscript & Superscript Tag

Used to display a horizontal ruler, used to separate content

<sub> subscript </sub>

<sup> superscript </sup>

H<sub>2</sub>O = H20 (2 in subscript)

A<sup>n</sup> + B = A^n+B (n in superscript)



viii) Pre Tag

Used to display text as it is (without ignoring spaces & next line)

<pre> This

is a sample

text.

</pre>



ix) Inside Main Tag

     a) Section Tag

        <section>
      
        For a section on your page
      
     b) Article Tag
      
        <article>
      
        For an article on your page
      
     c) Aside Tag
      
        <aside>
      
        For content aside main content(ads)



x) Revisiting Anchor Tag

<a href="https://google.com" target="_main"> Google </a>
                                      ||
                                  (for new tab)

<a href="https://google.com"> <img src="link"> </a>
                                      ||
                                 (clickable pic)



xi) Revisiting Image Tag

set height

set width

<img src="link" height=50px >

<img src="link" width=50px >

// we set only thing at a time so that the system automatically maintains the aspect ratio.



xii) Div Tag

Div is a container used for other HTML elements

Block Element (takes full width)(imp)



